  "body": "### Description\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: When user sends a word that is underlined by the spelling checker in Android, the same word appears again in the input after after typing new message. It happes only for the underlined words like: \r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/36553294-3ad0f1fa-17fc-11e8-8716-66ef13057249.png\" width=\"300\">\r\n\r\nNow, when user tries to write a new message he the input is filled with the last one that was sent:\r\n \r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/36553419-841281ee-17fc-11e8-8d7b-980c974c76de.png\" width=\"300\">\r\n\r\n**Note** that it does not happen when the word is not underlined: \r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/36553216-09aae5a4-17fc-11e8-97f2-9ba373a27fbc.png\" width=\"300\">\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nInput is not filled with the last message that was sent.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nInput is filled with last message that was sent.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Go to a chat\r\n- Write a word which will be \"underlined\" by Android\r\n- Sent it\r\n- Start writing a new message\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly, Feb 22\r\n* Operating System: Android 7.0\r\n* Was not tested on iOS\r\n* Device: Samsung Galaxy S8",
